      "widgets_values": [
        "=== PIi-CHAN EXPRESSION WORKFLOW ===\n\nHOW TO USE:\n\n1. FIRST TIME SETUP:\n   - Load your base checkpoint (Animagine XL, Counterfeit, etc.)\n   - Load IP-Adapter Plus Face model\n   - Load CLIP Vision model\n\n2. CREATE REFERENCE:\n   - Generate or load your ideal pii-chan neutral image\n   - Save it as 'pii-chan_reference.png'\n   - This locks the character design\n\n3. GENERATE EXPRESSIONS:\n   Change the [EXPRESSION: ...] part in the positive prompt:\n\n   neutral:   [EXPRESSION: calm expression, slight smile, looking at viewer]\n   happy:     [EXPRESSION: happy, big smile, closed eyes, blush, sparkles]\n   sad:       [EXPRESSION: sad expression, frown, downcast eyes, tears]\n   surprised: [EXPRESSION: surprised, wide eyes, open mouth, shocked, !]\n   thinking:  [EXPRESSION: thinking, looking up, finger on chin, pondering]\n   sleepy:    [EXPRESSION: sleepy, half-closed eyes, drowsy, tired, zzz]\n   talking:   [EXPRESSION: talking, open mouth, speaking, mid-sentence]\n   excited:   [EXPRESSION: very happy, excited, sparkle eyes, grin, jumping]\n   confused:  [EXPRESSION: confused, head tilt, raised eyebrow, question mark]\n\n4. TIPS:\n   - Keep same seed for consistency (or try different seeds)\n   - IP-Adapter weight 0.8-0.9 works well\n   - If face drifts, increase IP-Adapter weight\n   - Use same prompt prefix, only change [EXPRESSION: ...]\n"
      ],
      "title": "Instructions"
    }
